Effective implementation of the contractor safety program is accomplished by providing contractors with an orientation session that covers (1) a process overview, (2) information about the safety and health hazards, (3) emergency response plan requirements and (4) safe work practices prior to beginning their work. 

The date of most recent review of contractor safety procedures was at January 3, 2018. The date of the most recent evaluation of contractor safety performance was June 19, 2017. 

Propane Regulatory Framework:  The Facility implements the provisions of the following guidelines and regulations for this regulated substance. 

- API 650 & 620 - Tank Construction;
- ASME Boiler and Pressure Vessel Code, Section VIII;
- ASME B31.3 - Process Piping;
- Nevada Administrative Code (NAC) of Regulations, Chapter 459; 
- National Fire Protection Association (NFPA) 58 - Liquefied Petroleum Gas Code; 2014 edition; 
- NFPA 70 - National Electrical Code; 
- RMA Standard Number M-5;
- United States Environmental Protection Agency (U.S. EPA) 48 CFR 68; and 
- United States Department of Labor, Occupational Safety and Health Administration (OSHA), 29 CFR 1910.110, Storage and Handling of Liquefied Petroleum Gases.

FIVE-YEAR ACCIDENT HISTORY
Over the past five years there have been no large or small releases which have resulted in any injuries, property damage or offsite consequences. An incident investigation program is in place at the Facility and incident investigations would be implemented if needed. 

