Incident Investigation:  The Reno Terminal has procedures in place that require prompt investigation of incidents that resulted in or could have reasonably resulted in, a fire/explosion, major property damage, environmental loss, or personal injury. The investigation team documents its findings, develops recommendation(s) to prevent a recurrence and presents these results to the business management team for resolution. 

Employee Participation:  The Facility must rely upon the operational expertise and training of its employees at all levels and disciplines to ensure safe operations. The Facility has implemented procedures regarding employee participation to ensure consideration of their knowledge and experience in all applicable areas of the prevention program. The most recent revision of employee participation plans was January 3, 2018.

Hot Work Permit:  With regard to hot work that may occur on or near the propane process, the Reno Terminal has developed a written contractor evaluation program and a Hot Work Permit program to document the evaluation of the fire prevention and protection requirements. The Hot Work Permit system is implemented prior to allowing activities that could result the generation of sparks (e.g. cutting and grinding) or that involve the use of open flames.

The date of recent review of hot work permit procedures was at July 13, 2017.

